{
  "id": 5146458504429568,
  "name": "The revert-rule keyword",
  "summary": "The revert-rule keyword rolls back the cascade to the previous rule, similar to how revert-layer rolls back the cascade to the previous layer. For example:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndiv { color: green; }\r\ndiv { color: revert-rule; /* Effectively green */ }\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is especially useful in combination with conditionals, as it allows eliminating the current rule if some condition is not met:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndiv {\r\n  display: if(style(--layout: fancy): grid; else: revert-rule);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
